Seven Killed, 18 Injured in Chechnya Suicide Attacks, RIA Says

-- B y   S a r a h   H a l l s
-- 
2011-08-30T22:07:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/seven-killed-18-injured-in-chechnya-suicide-attacks-ria-says.html
Seven people were killed and 18
wounded in two separate suicide attacks in Grozny, the capital
of Chechnya, today, RIA Novosti reported on its website, citing
Ramzan Kadyrov, head of the North Caucasus Republic.  Five police officers, an Emergency Ministry official and a
civilian were among those killed in the explosions, which
occurred 30 minutes apart at the same site, RIA Novosti said,
citing the leader.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Halls in London at 
